      "content": "Hey, I'm doing a practice exercise for my criminal law class on sentencing parity. I have two different defendant profiles for the same non-violent drug offense, and I need help identifying potential mitigating and aggravating factors for each to see how a judge might approach them differently.\n\nDefendant A: A 21-year-old male, raised in a stable, suburban environment, completed two years of college, and has a consistent history of local community service.\n\nDefendant B: A 21-year-old male, raised in an underserved urban environment, has a sporadic employment history, and no prior community involvement.\n\nCan you break down the mitigating and aggravating factors for both and suggest what kind of sentencing focus (rehabilitative vs punitive) might be applied to each?",
